#
# koto is the **Rust-based scripting language** by
# irh.  Dynamically-typed; embeddable; designed for
# scripting and animations.  Pivots from hand-rolled
# Rust (R273 irust) into the **pico_args minimalist
# Rust CLI cluster**.  Sister to Lua / Janet (R270 carp
# Lisp) / Wren (small embeddable languages).  **MAJOR
# MILESTONE**: corpus's **first documented pico_args
# Rust CLI** — adds a 5TH category to the Rust CLI
# library sub-taxonomy (now 5 sub-categories: clap
# derive / clap builder / clap v3 / hand-rolled / **pico_args**).
#
# Critical extraction note: koto uses **`pico_args`**
# library at `pico_args::Arguments::from_env()`
# (main.rs:77) — corpus's **first documented
# `pico_args` Rust CLI**.  pico_args is a **minimalist
# Rust CLI library** designed as an alternative to
# clap — much smaller (~1500 LOC vs clap's 100K+ LOC)
# and faster to compile (~50ms vs clap's ~2s).  Trade-
# offs: no auto-help generation, no validation, no
# subcommand routing, no ValueEnum.  Documents the
# **5-way Rust CLI library sub-taxonomy**: (a) clap
# derive (R247-R262, R268 — declarative, full-featured),
# (b) clap builder (R259 hyperfine — imperative, full-
# featured), (c) clap v3 (R261 replibyte — older clap),
# (d) hand-rolled (R273 irust — no library at all),
# (e) **pico_args** (R274 koto — minimalist library).
# **Rust CLI sub-taxonomy NOW COMPLETE** via R273+R274
# cluster: 5 categories covering the full spectrum
# from heavyweight (clap) to lightweight (pico_args)
# to none (hand-rolled).  Documents the **CLI library
# weight spectrum** — clap is the standard for full-
# featured CLIs; pico_args is the standard for "I want
# a library but minimal overhead"; hand-rolled is the
# minimum.
#
# Critical extraction note: koto uses
# **`args.contains([short, long])`** at main.rs:79-88
# — pico_args's flag-detection API takes a tuple of
# short and long names.  E.g. `args.contains(["-e",
# "--eval"])` returns `true` if either `-e` or `--eval`
# is in the args.  Documents the **pico_args tuple-
# argument flag-detection pattern** — distinct from
# clap derive's `#[arg(short = 'e', long = "eval")]`
# attribute declaration and from R273 irust's
# `match` `|` pattern.  Plus pico_args methods CONSUME
# the matching args from the internal arg list — so
# calling `contains` for the same flag twice returns
# `false` the second time.  Documents the **destructive-
# parse** pattern in pico_args.
#
# Critical extraction note: koto uses
# **`args.opt_value_from_str(["-c", "--config"])?`** at
# main.rs:85 — pico_args's value-taking option API
# returning `Result<Option<T>>`.  The `from_str` suffix
# uses `T::from_str` to parse the value; alternatives
# include `from_fn` (custom parser fn) and `from_os_str`
# (raw OsString).  Documents the **pico_args value-
# parsing API trio** — corpus's first documented
# pico_args option API.
#
# Critical extraction note: koto uses
# **`args.subcommand()`** at main.rs:90 — pico_args
# terminology where the FIRST POSITIONAL NON-FLAG ARG
# is called the "subcommand" (even though koto doesn't
# use it as a true subcommand — it's actually the
# script path / source).  Documents the **pico_args
# subcommand-as-first-positional** convention —
# distinct from clap derive's `#[arg]` positional
# (which is just a named arg) and from R273 irust's
# heuristic `.rs` extension check.  Plus pico_args has
# `free_from_str()` / `free_from_fn()` for typed
# positionals; koto uses `subcommand()` which returns
# `Option<String>`.  Corpus's **first documented
# `pico_args::subcommand()` API**.
#
# Critical extraction note: koto uses **`args.finish()`**
# at main.rs:93 — pico_args's "give me the rest"
# method.  Returns `Vec<OsString>` of all remaining
# args after the parsed flags/options/subcommand are
# consumed.  koto uses this for script_args (args
# forwarded to the script's `koto.args`).  Documents
# the **pico_args finish-and-collect-remaining pattern**
# — distinct from R263 lazygit's flaggy `flaggy.Args()`
# (Go) and from R266 uvicorn's Click variadic argument.
# Plus koto's `finish().drain(..).map(|s| s.into_string()
# ).collect::<Result<_, _>>()` converts OsString to
# String, bailing on non-UTF8 strings.  Documents the
# **OsString-to-String conversion pattern** for CLI
# args.
#
# Critical extraction note: koto uses **stdin-as-input
# detection** at main.rs:167-172 — same as R273 irust!
# When no script arg is provided AND stdin is NOT a
# TTY (i.e., it's piped), koto reads stdin to EOF and
# treats it as the script source.  Documents the
# **convergent design pattern**: both irust (R273) and
# koto (R274) — independently — implement the SAME
# stdin-as-input auto-detection.  This pattern is now
# documented in TWO corpus rounds, suggesting it's the
# **idiomatic Unix-tool pattern** for "no args + pipe =
# read from pipe".

